Dialogue: 0,0:00:00.00,0:01:29.98,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,
Dialogue: 0,0:02:11.26,0:02:15.81,Magus-Flashback-internal,A,0000,0000,0000,,You're going to ruin her if you continue to \Ndo nothing more than let her live with you.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:22.46,0:02:23.71,Default,Chesi,0000,0000,0000,,Elias...
Dialogue: 0,0:02:23.90,0:02:24.90,Default,Old Man,0000,0000,0000,,That's right.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:24.90,0:02:29.12,Default,Old Man,0000,0000,0000,,His name was given to him by my master.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:30.47,0:02:37.33,Magus-Flashback,Doctor Who,0000,0000,0000,,Welcome, Elias, to this dizzying, \Ndisgusting, beautiful world.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:39.88,0:02:42.14,Magus-Flashback,Doctor Who,0000,0000,0000,,All right, take care of Elias for me,
Dialogue: 0,0:02:43.51,0:02:44.60,Magus-Flashback,Doctor Who,0000,0000,0000,,Lindel.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:52.77,0:02:54.43,Magus-Flashback,Old Man,0000,0000,0000,,This is all so sudden.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:55.60,0:02:58.90,Magus-Flashback,Old Man,0000,0000,0000,,Well, from now on, you're Elias.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:02.00,0:03:08.60,Default,Old Man,0000,0000,0000,,For a few years, the two of us traveled \Nthe forest, chasing reindeer.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:09.11,0:03:13.25,Default,Old Man,0000,0000,0000,,We traveled, enjoying the sight of \Nthe lakes and fields as we went.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:26.48,0:03:28.77,Magus-Flashback,Old Man,0000,0000,0000,,Hey, what are you doing?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:28.77,0:03:31.40,Magus-Flashback,Old Man,0000,0000,0000,,You shouldn't take things you \Naren't even going to eat.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:31.80,0:03:32.85,Magus-Flashback,Elias Beta,0000,0000,0000,,I shouldn't?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:34.79,0:03:38.66,Default,Old Man,0000,0000,0000,,Elias seemed to be missing something.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:39.17,0:03:43.82,Default,Old Man,0000,0000,0000,,He learned quickly, but he seemed as though \Nhe was looking at everything from the outside.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:44.68,0:03:49.32,Default,Old Man,0000,0000,0000,,One day, when we were running \Nlow on food, we visited a home.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:50.49,0:03:53.46,Magus-Flashback,Old Man,0000,0000,0000,,Hello, I'm a shaman.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:53.68,0:03:56.70,Magus-Flashback,Old Man,0000,0000,0000,,Is there anyone sick or injured here?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:57.08,0:04:01.34,Magus-Flashback,Old Man,0000,0000,0000,,Would you spare me some food \Nin exchange for healing?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:04.97,0:04:08.29,Magus-Flashback,Sakamoto Ryuichi,0000,0000,0000,,My grandson happens to be bedridden.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:10.13,0:04:14.09,Magus-Flashback,Old Man,0000,0000,0000,,I can make use of my hands for a fever.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:29.61,0:04:30.88,Magus-Flashback,Old Man,0000,0000,0000,,It must be awful for you.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:31.21,0:04:32.36,Magus-Flashback,Old Man,0000,0000,0000,,You'll be better soon.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:33.11,0:04:34.79,Magus-Flashback,Old Man,0000,0000,0000,,Sleep well.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:39.79,0:04:41.06,Magus-Flashback,Old Man,0000,0000,0000,,You're his little sister?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:41.89,0:04:43.58,Magus-Flashback,Old Man,0000,0000,0000,,Don't worry.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:43.58,0:04:44.67,Magus-Flashback,Old Man,0000,0000,0000,,Your brother will be fine.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:46.67,0:04:47.59,Magus-Flashback,A,0000,0000,0000,,That man...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:48.49,0:04:50.70,Magus-Flashback,A,0000,0000,0000,,There's something in his shadow.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:54.20,0:04:54.72,Magus-Flashback,A,0000,0000,0000,,I'm scared!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:55.58,0:04:56.72,Magus-Flashback,Sakamoto Ryuichi,0000,0000,0000,,What is it?!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:58.17,0:04:59.35,Magus-Flashback,Mom,0000,0000,0000,,It's a monster!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:01.06,0:05:02.35,Magus-Flashback,Mom,0000,0000,0000,,A m-monster!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:02.54,0:05:03.19,Magus-Flashback,Old Man,0000,0000,0000,,Hurry!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:04.86,0:05:05.72,Magus-Flashback,Sakamoto Ryuichi,0000,0000,0000,,It's evil!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:05.72,0:05:06.61,Magus-Flashback,A,0000,0000,0000,,It's a demon!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:06.61,0:05:09.11,Magus-Flashback,B,0000,0000,0000,,He was going to take the kid!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:09.11,0:05:11.05,Magus-Flashback,Old Man,0000,0000,0000,,There was a child with the sight in the house.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:11.05,0:05:11.61,Magus-Flashback,Old Man,0000,0000,0000,,Shit.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:12.38,0:05:13.57,Magus-Flashback,Elias Beta,0000,0000,0000,,Sorry, Lindel.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:13.57,0:05:15.25,Magus-Flashback,Old Man,0000,0000,0000,,It's not your fault.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:16.05,0:05:17.20,Magus-Flashback,A,0000,0000,0000,,You demon!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:19.92,0:05:21.06,Magus-Flashback,B,0000,0000,0000,,Demon!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:24.33,0:05:26.15,Magus-Flashback,C,0000,0000,0000,,I'll kill you!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:28.21,0:05:29.43,Magus-Flashback,B,0000,0000,0000,,Evil!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:31.31,0:05:32.25,Magus-Flashback,A,0000,0000,0000,,Demon!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:32.37,0:05:33.40,Magus-Flashback,A,0000,0000,0000,,Demon!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:33.40,0:05:35.05,Magus-Flashback,A,0000,0000,0000,,I'll kill you!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:54.16,0:05:54.99,Magus-Flashback,D,0000,0000,0000,,Send for help!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:58.50,0:06:00.25,Magus-Flashback,Old Man,0000,0000,0000,,Stop, Elias!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:02.63,0:06:07.49,Magus-Flashback,Old Man,0000,0000,0000,,Veil of the forest, lift yourself for us!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:15.37,0:06:16.57,Magus-Flashback,A,0000,0000,0000,,He's gone.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:29.89,0:06:31.09,Magus-Flashback,Elias Beta,0000,0000,0000,,Where are we?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:35.82,0:06:39.08,Magus-Flashback,Old Man,0000,0000,0000,,This is where the forest gods live.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:45.05,0:06:46.16,Magus-Flashback,Elias Beta,0000,0000,0000,,Lindel.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:48.51,0:06:51.78,Magus-Flashback,Old Man,0000,0000,0000,,This is what happens when \NI force myself to use magic.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:52.48,0:06:54.70,Magus-Flashback,Old Man,0000,0000,0000,,We need to get out of here.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:18.05,0:07:19.18,Magus-Flashback-internal,Old Man,0000,0000,0000,,Spruce.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:23.55,0:07:28.21,Magus-Flashback,Elias Beta,0000,0000,0000,,Take us outside, to Lindel's reindeer.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:31.93,0:07:34.50,Magus-Flashback-internal,Old Man,0000,0000,0000,,I taught him that.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:59.02,0:08:02.08,Magus-Flashback,Old Man,0000,0000,0000,,You're surprisingly good with your hands.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:04.62,0:08:07.54,Magus-Flashback,Elias Beta,0000,0000,0000,,I've seen you do this lots of times.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:09.31,0:08:10.45,Magus-Flashback,Old Man,0000,0000,0000,,Thanks.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:16.94,0:08:18.59,Magus-Flashback,Old Man,0000,0000,0000,,Is something wrong?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:19.31,0:08:20.31,Magus-Flashback,Elias Beta,0000,0000,0000,,Lindel,
Dialogue: 0,0:08:22.23,0:08:28.32,Magus-Flashback,Elias Beta,0000,0000,0000,,I'm pretty sure I've eaten humans before.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:46.51,0:08:48.32,Default,Old Man,0000,0000,0000,,What do you think, Chise?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:48.32,0:08:51.00,Default,Old Man,0000,0000,0000,,What if he's a man-eating monster?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:06.33,0:09:12.36,Default,Chesi,0000,0000,0000,,I could see things from the other \Nside ever since I was little.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:12.81,0:09:16.77,Default,Chesi,0000,0000,0000,,A lot of them would talk about \Nhow tasty or gross humans are.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:18.37,0:09:20.60,Default,Chesi,0000,0000,0000,,I was really scared.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:23.32,0:09:28.76,Default,Chesi,0000,0000,0000,,But Elias has never scared me, not once.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:30.82,0:09:35.63,Default,Chesi,0000,0000,0000,,So, if he really used to...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:39.18,0:09:42.09,Default,Old Man,0000,0000,0000,,Tell him the rest yourself.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:42.87,0:09:45.04,Default,Chesi,0000,0000,0000,,But you were the one who asked.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:45.32,0:09:46.80,Default,Old Man,0000,0000,0000,,My bad.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:48.82,0:09:51.11,Default,Old Man,0000,0000,0000,,You're well-spoken.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:51.50,0:09:54.48,Default,Old Man,0000,0000,0000,,You should talk to him lots, too.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:56.14,0:09:58.74,Default,Chesi,0000,0000,0000,,What did you say in response, Lindel?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:58.74,0:09:59.79,Default,Old Man,0000,0000,0000,,Me?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:59.79,0:10:00.82,Default,Old Man,0000,0000,0000,,I said...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:01.92,0:10:04.66,Magus-Flashback,Old Man,0000,0000,0000,,I bet I'm tasty. Don't eat me.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:07.37,0:10:09.52,Magus-Flashback,Elias Beta,0000,0000,0000,,I'm... not going to eat you.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:09.52,0:10:10.58,Magus-Flashback,Old Man,0000,0000,0000,,Okay, good.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:11.67,0:10:15.32,Magus-Flashback,Elias Beta,0000,0000,0000,,But sometimes I feel the urge to...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:15.97,0:10:17.55,Magus-Flashback,Elias Beta,0000,0000,0000,,Even though I'm sure I don't really want to.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:18.20,0:10:21.44,Magus-Flashback,Elias Beta,0000,0000,0000,,Aren't humans afraid of things like me?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:22.08,0:10:26.18,Magus-Flashback,Old Man,0000,0000,0000,,Hey, there are lots of \Nthings that eat humans.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:26.66,0:10:30.16,Magus-Flashback,Old Man,0000,0000,0000,,I have no reason to be fearful \Nof you in particular.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:32.19,0:10:35.57,Magus-Flashback,Old Man,0000,0000,0000,,Eat all kinds of things, and soon enough,
Dialogue: 0,0:10:35.57,0:10:38.82,Magus-Flashback,Old Man,0000,0000,0000,,you'll forget all about your \Nambivalent taste for humans.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:40.59,0:10:44.38,Default,Old Man,0000,0000,0000,,I kind of killed the \Nconversation on purpose.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:44.77,0:10:46.75,Default,Old Man,0000,0000,0000,,I was actually scared, after all.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:47.79,0:10:49.34,Default,Chesi,0000,0000,0000,,You were, huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:49.79,0:10:52.04,Default,Old Man,0000,0000,0000,,You'd be shocked, too, at least for a moment,
Dialogue: 0,0:10:52.04,0:10:55.59,Default,Old Man,0000,0000,0000,,if you found out that the cat curled up on \Nyour lap actually ate humans, wouldn't you?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:56.75,0:10:58.16,Magus-Internal/narrator,Chesi,0000,0000,0000,,Comparing him to a cat?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:59.96,0:11:05.03,Default,Old Man,0000,0000,0000,,Either way, my fears vanished as \Nsoon as I took a sip of the soup.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:06.64,0:11:10.39,Default,Old Man,0000,0000,0000,,Also, that soup tasted unbelievably bad.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:13.48,0:11:15.68,Magus-Internal/narrator,Chesi,0000,0000,0000,,Thank goodness for Silky.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:16.58,0:11:22.30,Default,Old Man,0000,0000,0000,,Still, humans are the most easily-scared \Nand cruel creatures of all.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:23.32,0:11:28.44,Default,Old Man,0000,0000,0000,,I told him he shouldn't tell \Npeople about it too much.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:28.66,0:11:34.29,Default,Old Man,0000,0000,0000,,I don't know if he's following my advice, \Nor if something else happened...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:34.69,0:11:38.46,Default,Old Man,0000,0000,0000,,But he absolutely refuses to \Ntell people about himself.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:40.14,0:11:42.61,Default,Old Man,0000,0000,0000,,He's still stuck as a child.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:43.58,0:11:45.63,Default,Old Man,0000,0000,0000,,Sorry for the long talk.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:45.98,0:11:47.52,Default,Old Man,0000,0000,0000,,You should get some sleep.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:54.60,0:11:57.28,Default,Dawg,0000,0000,0000,,Can't sleep, Chise?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:57.58,0:12:00.31,Default,Chesi,0000,0000,0000,,Nah, thanks, Ruth.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:04.36,0:12:08.15,Magus-Internal/narrator,Chesi,0000,0000,0000,,Did I look tasty?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:11.46,0:12:15.04,Magus-Internal/narrator,Chesi,0000,0000,0000,,I guess I've heard something \Nhe didn't want to say.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:23.91,0:12:24.71,Default,Old Man,0000,0000,0000,,It's morning.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:26.87,0:12:29.44,Default,Chesi,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, right, I'm in the land of dragons.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:32.93,0:12:34.92,Default,Chesi,0000,0000,0000,,Good morning.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:35.37,0:12:36.64,Default,Old Man,0000,0000,0000,,Morning.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:38.87,0:12:39.97,Default,A,0000,0000,0000,,Chise!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:39.97,0:12:40.94,Default,B,0000,0000,0000,,Human!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:40.94,0:12:42.17,Default,C,0000,0000,0000,,Morning!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:41.43,0:12:42.82,Default,D,0000,0000,0000,,Morning!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:42.12,0:12:43.12,Default,E,0000,0000,0000,,{\a6}Morning.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:43.12,0:12:43.92,Default,Chesi,0000,0000,0000,,Morning—
Dialogue: 0,0:12:49.61,0:12:51.00,Default,Dawg,0000,0000,0000,,Chise!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:51.32,0:12:53.70,Default,Old Man,0000,0000,0000,,That girl sure does fall into water a lot.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:20.74,0:13:22.55,Default,Dawg,0000,0000,0000,,Chise, are you all right?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:23.09,0:13:25.31,Default,Chesi,0000,0000,0000,,There was this amazing thing.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:28.93,0:13:31.50,Default,Chesi,0000,0000,0000,,Why are you cutting my hair?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:31.50,0:13:35.25,Default,Old Man,0000,0000,0000,,Even since long ago, hair \Nhas always carried magic.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:35.52,0:13:37.60,Default,Old Man,0000,0000,0000,,We'll use this as the core of the wand.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:37.94,0:13:41.25,Default,Old Man,0000,0000,0000,,You don't see many Asians \Nwith red hair like yours.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:41.60,0:13:43.98,Default,Old Man,0000,0000,0000,,It's a perfect color for magic.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:44.97,0:13:46.76,Default,Old Man,0000,0000,0000,,Red is the color of the earth,
Dialogue: 0,0:13:47.09,0:13:50.01,Default,Old Man,0000,0000,0000,,the color of the flames and blood \Nflowing through the stars.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:50.49,0:13:52.47,Default,Old Man,0000,0000,0000,,Choose a handpiece from one of these.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:53.56,0:13:57.39,Default,Old Man,0000,0000,0000,,The red elderberry knocks on the \Ndoor to the black goddess.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:57.91,0:14:01.90,Default,Old Man,0000,0000,0000,,The willow lingers between \Nthe living and the dead.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:02.47,0:14:06.05,Default,Old Man,0000,0000,0000,,The hazel wards off evil.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:06.49,0:14:08.63,Default,Old Man,0000,0000,0000,,The yew is a symbol of eternity.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:08.63,0:14:11.15,Default,Old Man,0000,0000,0000,,It can draw or banish magic.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:11.47,0:14:16.05,Default,Old Man,0000,0000,0000,,The checker tree has a powerful life \Nforce and brings order to the wicked.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:18.51,0:14:20.84,Default,Chesi,0000,0000,0000,,I saw him when I first came here.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:26.30,0:14:29.33,Default,Old Man,0000,0000,0000,,I had him dry the wood out.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:29.72,0:14:32.35,Default,Old Man,0000,0000,0000,,Well, let's get to carving.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:35.22,0:14:39.31,Default,Old Man,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, sorry, there's nothing \Nfor me to teach you.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:40.17,0:14:43.56,Default,Old Man,0000,0000,0000,,Just carve it as you like, so that \Nit's comfortable for you to use.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:44.39,0:14:49.16,Default,Old Man,0000,0000,0000,,It's customary for one to carve their own \Nwands, and for their senior to finish it.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:49.72,0:14:53.25,Default,Old Man,0000,0000,0000,,It would be good to talk to \Nyourself as you're carving.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:53.82,0:14:55.26,Default,Chesi,0000,0000,0000,,To myself?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:55.26,0:14:57.48,Default,Old Man,0000,0000,0000,,I'll go take a look around.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:57.48,0:14:59.48,Default,Old Man,0000,0000,0000,,Take your time.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:10.90,0:15:13.06,Magus-Internal/narrator,Chesi,0000,0000,0000,,Talk to myself?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:16.18,0:15:18.55,Default,Dawg,0000,0000,0000,,You have to talk to {\i1}yourself{\i0}, don't you?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:19.16,0:15:20.94,Default,Chesi,0000,0000,0000,,Ruth...
Dialogue: 0,0:15:38.66,0:15:45.46,Magus-Internal/narrator,Chesi,0000,0000,0000,,I guess I've never really thought \Nabout myself until now.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:26.68,0:16:28.20,Default,Old Man,0000,0000,0000,,It's dark now.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:28.20,0:16:29.07,Default,Old Man,0000,0000,0000,,Take a break.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:30.10,0:16:32.26,Default,Old Man,0000,0000,0000,,That's some amazing focus.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:32.55,0:16:34.49,Default,Old Man,0000,0000,0000,,You're almost done.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:35.26,0:16:35.88,Default,Chesi,0000,0000,0000,,Right.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:36.39,0:16:38.62,Default,Chesi,0000,0000,0000,,Just a little more work.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:40.15,0:16:43.38,Default,Old Man,0000,0000,0000,,Not bad at all, for a beginner.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:43.38,0:16:44.80,Default,Old Man,0000,0000,0000,,Let's finish it tomorrow.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:50.36,0:16:52.63,Default,Old Man,0000,0000,0000,,The moon's bright tonight.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:53.01,0:16:55.12,Default,Old Man,0000,0000,0000,,I can show you something nice.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:57.46,0:16:59.61,Default,Old Man,0000,0000,0000,,The moss here grows flowers.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:59.83,0:17:00.84,Default,Chesi,0000,0000,0000,,Flowers?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:01.23,0:17:03.10,Default,Old Man,0000,0000,0000,,The elves created this land.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:03.10,0:17:04.33,Default,Old Man,0000,0000,0000,,They adore it.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:04.70,0:17:07.28,Default,Old Man,0000,0000,0000,,Dance with the elves, and \Nthe flowers will bloom.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:07.75,0:17:10.12,Default,Old Man,0000,0000,0000,,Do you know my other name?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:10.12,0:17:13.57,Default,Chesi,0000,0000,0000,,Echos, the song of a hundred flowers?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:13.57,0:17:18.61,Default,Old Man,0000,0000,0000,,Names are very important \Nfor mages and sorcerers.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:18.88,0:17:22.51,Default,Old Man,0000,0000,0000,,Usually, they're called by the name that \Ndescribes their features and their true nature.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:29.26,0:17:31.81,Default,Old Man,0000,0000,0000,,My spells are songs.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:33.42,0:17:36.15,Default,Old Man,0000,0000,0000,,Let's have them bloom \Nfor us, just for tonight.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:18.80,0:18:24.27,Magus-Internal/narrator,Chesi,0000,0000,0000,,Like snowmelt, it was both low and high.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:24.27,0:18:26.17,Magus-Internal/narrator,Chesi,0000,0000,0000,,It resonated through the wind.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:28.75,0:18:29.64,Default,A,0000,0000,0000,,Let's dance.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:29.75,0:18:30.65,Default,B,0000,0000,0000,,Let's dance.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:30.65,0:18:32.01,Default,Chesi,0000,0000,0000,,Elves?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:32.01,0:18:33.59,Default,Chesi,0000,0000,0000,,I've never danced before.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:34.12,0:18:36.88,Default,Alien Gremlin Shaman,0000,0000,0000,,Just twirl around with them.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:37.63,0:18:41.05,Default,Old Man,0000,0000,0000,,Listen carefully to the sound, to the song,
Dialogue: 0,0:18:41.05,0:18:44.10,Default,Old Man,0000,0000,0000,,to the sound of the wind, \Nto the sound of the water.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:44.68,0:18:47.94,Default,Old Man,0000,0000,0000,,Humanity still remembers the sounds
Dialogue: 0,0:18:47.94,0:18:51.48,Default,Old Man,0000,0000,0000,,that filled our bodies from long \Nago, before even language itself.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:59.12,0:19:00.90,Default,Old Man,0000,0000,0000,,Magic is the same way.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:01.55,0:19:04.74,Default,Old Man,0000,0000,0000,,Listen to what is around you, \Nand offer out your hand.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:05.30,0:19:07.41,Default,Old Man,0000,0000,0000,,You still remember that.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:29.22,0:19:31.01,Default,Chesi,0000,0000,0000,,I'm spent.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:53.72,0:19:58.41,Magus-Internal/narrator,Chesi,0000,0000,0000,,I wonder what {\i0}he{\i1} would say,\N if he saw this scene.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:01.36,0:20:02.61,Default,Chesi,0000,0000,0000,,Elias.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:04.56,0:20:05.47,Magus-Internal/narrator,Elias,0000,0000,0000,,Chise.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:05.70,0:20:07.58,Magus-Internal/narrator,Elias,0000,0000,0000,,Why did you make a water mirror?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:07.89,0:20:09.14,Default,Chesi,0000,0000,0000,,A water mirror?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:09.57,0:20:13.49,Default,Elias,0000,0000,0000,,A water mirror lets you see \Na person through the water.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:15.20,0:20:15.92,Default,Elias,0000,0000,0000,,Huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:16.54,0:20:18.32,Default,Elias,0000,0000,0000,,Is he singing right now?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:18.32,0:20:19.15,Magus-Internal/narrator,Chesi,0000,0000,0000,,Yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:19.68,0:20:20.89,Default,Elias,0000,0000,0000,,No wonder.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:21.40,0:20:24.84,Default,Elias,0000,0000,0000,,His magic connected there to here.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:25.34,0:20:26.86,Magus-Internal/narrator,Chesi,0000,0000,0000,,I see.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:27.84,0:20:29.01,Magus-Internal/narrator,Chesi,0000,0000,0000,,Elias...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:29.28,0:20:30.12,Default,Elias,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:31.54,0:20:34.60,Magus-Internal/narrator,Chesi,0000,0000,0000,,You look troubled.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:34.97,0:20:36.75,Magus-Internal/narrator,Chesi,0000,0000,0000,,Did something happen?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:38.11,0:20:39.50,Default,Elias,0000,0000,0000,,I suppose.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:39.50,0:20:40.16,Default,Elias,0000,0000,0000,,A little.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:41.11,0:20:42.17,Default,Chesi,0000,0000,0000,,Is everything okay?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:46.79,0:20:51.88,Default,Elias,0000,0000,0000,,Home is a bit cold without you.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:52.89,0:20:55.84,Default,Elias,0000,0000,0000,,Even though it's summer, \Nand I have the stove on.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:01.15,0:21:03.90,Default,Chesi,0000,0000,0000,,The flowers are beautiful here.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:04.39,0:21:06.61,Default,Chesi,0000,0000,0000,,I wish I could show you.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:07.46,0:21:10.91,Magus-Internal/narrator,Elias,0000,0000,0000,,Take them in, and tell me about \Nthem when you get back.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:16.79,0:21:18.36,Default,Chesi,0000,0000,0000,,Here's a small taste.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:31.89,0:21:33.10,Magus-Internal/narrator,Chesi,0000,0000,0000,,Elias,
Dialogue: 0,0:21:33.89,0:21:38.15,Default,Chesi,0000,0000,0000,,I heard all kinds of things about you.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:39.24,0:21:41.11,Magus-Internal/narrator,Elias,0000,0000,0000,,That old bastard...
Dialogue: 0,0:21:41.51,0:21:47.62,Default,Chesi,0000,0000,0000,,So I'll tell you what I haven't \Nbeen able to tell you, too.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:50.36,0:21:52.95,Default,Chesi,0000,0000,0000,,I'll head home as soon as my wand's done.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:53.50,0:21:54.40,Magus-Internal/narrator,Elias,0000,0000,0000,,Okay.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:54.40,0:21:55.36,Magus-Internal/narrator,Elias,0000,0000,0000,,Please.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:00.28,0:22:02.13,Magus-Internal/narrator,Old Man,0000,0000,0000,,Two kids.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:02.13,0:22:06.48,Magus-Internal/narrator,Old Man,0000,0000,0000,,I don't even have kids, but \NI feel like I'm raising both of them.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:55.78,0:24:02.19,Default,Chesi,0000,0000,0000,,A girl who hadn't a place to return is \Nshown the way by Lindenbaum's staff.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:02.19,0:24:05.21,Default,Chesi,0000,0000,0000,,What does she choose at \Nthe end of her wandering?
Dialogue: 0,0:24:05.82,0:24:09.01,Default,Chesi,0000,0000,0000,,Please... Connect me to that person.
